# ClineFlow Reference System Configuration
# Copy this file to .clineflow.local and edit with your repository paths
#
# 💡 PRO TIP: Instead of manual setup, you can ask Cline:
#    "I need to setup cline refs to project-a and project-b 
#     which live in the parent folder. Can you help me?"
#
# Cline will create this config and run setup-refs.sh automatically!

# Example: Backend API repository
# BACKEND_API_PATH="/Users/yourname/projects/backend-api"

# Example: Frontend application repository
# FRONTEND_APP_PATH="/Users/yourname/projects/frontend-app"

# Example: Shared library repository
# SHARED_LIB_PATH="/Users/yourname/projects/shared-library"

# Add more repositories as needed
# Variable names must end with _PATH
# The symlink name will be derived from the variable name
# Example: BACKEND_API_PATH → clineflow/backend-api
